'''Carole Landis''' (born January 1st 1919-died July 5 1948) was an [[United States|American]] [[actress]] who acted mostly in [[movie]]s. Her movies include ''Fly Away Baby'' and ''Broadway Melody of 1938''. She was born near [[Eau Claire, Wisconsin]]. Landis later took her life by overdose of drugs.
