[[Image:Rachel Roberts.JPG|thumb|upright|Rachel Roberts in 1970s]] '''Rachel Roberts''' (September 20, 1927 - November 26, 1980) was a [[Welsh people|Welsh]] [[actress]] who starred in many [[movie]]s and stage acts. She became well-known for her fervour and strong passion. She starred in the 1953 movie ''Valley of Song''. While in [[Los Angeles]], Roberts committed [[suicide]] at age 53 with [[barbiturate]]s and [[alcohol]].
